text: Santa Bárbara (Portuguese for Saint Barbara) is a parish in the municipality of Ribeira Grande in the Azores. The population in 2011 was 1,275,Instituto Nacional de Estatística in an area of 12.84 km².Eurostat It contains the localities Chavinha, Courela, Diogo and Santa Bárbara. ==References== Category:Parishes of Ribeira Grande, Azores
title: Santa Bárbara (Ribeira Grande)
